# Analysis of Fixed Income Securities

## Introduction to Fixed Income Securities

[Fixed income securities](../Clippings/Bond%20Equivalent%20Yield%20(BEY)%20-%20Definition,%20Formula,%20and%20Example.md) are [financial instruments](../Financial%20Instruments/A%20Practical%20Guide%20for%20Actuaries%20and%20other%20Business%20Professionals..md) representing debt obligations with specific characteristics and [investment](../Advanced%20Investments/An%20Asset%20Allocation%20Primer.md) implications.

### Key Characteristics
- [Debt instruments](../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%2014/Corporate%20Bonds%20and%20Loans.md) representing financial obligations
- Provide periodic interest payments
- Return principal at maturity
- Vary in complexity and structure

### Types of Issuers
- Corporations
- Governments
- Municipal entities
- [Financial institutions](../Financial%20Markets%20and%20Institutions/Financial%20Markets%20and%20Institutions%20Lecture%20Notes.md)

